# Copy this file to ".env" and put local-only values there.
# ".env" is gitignored and must NEVER be committed.
#
# Why: a published plugin's bundle ships to every user and is fully readable.
# Real secrets belong on a backend (environment variables / a secrets manager)
# or in figma.clientStorage at runtime — never inside the plugin code, the UI,
# or the manifest.
#
# Uncomment and set these in your local .env only if your plugin needs them:
# BACKEND_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000
# FEATURE_BETA=false
